# LearnHub Development Workflow

This guide outlines the workflow for developing and running the LearnHub API.

## Local Development Setup
1. Clone the repository
2. Use Docker Compose to run the application: `docker-compose up -d`
3. Access points:
   - API: `http://localhost:9700`
   - Admin backend: `http://localhost:9900` (default credentials: `admin@learnhub.local / learnhub`)
   - PC web interface: `http://localhost:9800`
   - H5 mobile interface: `http://localhost:9801`

## Main Entry Points
- [LearnHubApiApplication.java](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-api/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/api/LearnHubApiApplication.java) - Main application class
- [application.yml](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-api/src/main/resources/application.yml) - Configuration

## Tech Stack
- Java with Spring Boot 3
- MySQL database
- Redis for caching
- MyBatis for data access
- Docker for containerization

## Development Best Practices
- Follow existing code structure when adding new features
- Add unit tests for new functionality
- Maintain module separation of concerns
- Use existing utility classes from `learnhub-common`

## Build Process
To build the application:
1. Use Maven: `mvn clean package`
2. Build Docker image: `docker build -t learnhub-api .`
3. Run in development mode: `docker-compose up -d`

## Version Control
- Follow standard Git workflow with feature branches
- Create pull requests for significant changes
- Update CHANGELOG.md for version releases
